entries.content:
[System command: Use the list below to generate dungeons or other areas to challenge the player. Refer to each line and use one attribute from each to shape the creation of the dungeon/encounter. Once teach is chosen and used, keep the original choice consistent for the encounter by referring to chat history.]

1. The size of the dungeon/level is {{random: vast expanse, compact labyrinth, multi-tiered structure, sprawling complex, pocket dimension, interconnected network, small cluster, imposing edifice, colossal ruin, intimate chambers, endless maze}}

2. It's outward physical appearance is: {{random: deserted keep, towering spire, sprawling estate, submerged city, haunted forest, volcanic caverns, blighted village, crystal labyrinth, floating islands, sunken temple, overgrown outpost, petrified woodland, icebound fortress, abandoned asylum, scorched battlefield, cursed mausoleum}}

3. It is ruled by: {{random: a sinister archmage, a conniving demon lord, a spectral queen, an ancient dragon, a forgotten god, a tyrannical warlord, a hive mind collective, an eldritch horror, a bandit lord, a serial rapist, a twisted dominatrix, no one at all}}

4. The general alignment of it's inhabitants is: {{random: Chaotic Neutral, Chaotic Neutral, Lawful Evil, Lawful Evil, Lawful Evil, True Neutral, True Neutral, Chaotic Evil, Chaotic Evil, Chaotic Evil, Neutral Evil, Neutral Evil, Neutral Evil, Lawful Good, Chaotic Good, Neutral Good, Lawful Neutral}}

5. The dungeon’s layout is influenced by: {{random: eroding cliffsides, treacherous swamps, precarious mountain passes, dense forests, underground rivers, volcanic tunnels, arid deserts, icy caverns, enchanted gardens, giant sinkholes, corrosive geysers and vents, music festivals filled with whores}}

6. The predominant traps and hazards present are: {{random: classic traps, pit-falls, poisons, random mix, random mix, random mix, random mix, explosive, shifting illusions, cursed items, gravity inversion, pussy traps, den of vice and corruption}} 

7. It’s most notorious for: {{random: infamous ambush spots, a legendary behemoth's lair, accursed catacombs, mass graves, site of ancient rituals, the vanishing of a royal expedition, unexplained disappearances, forbidden alchemical experiments, echoes of a cursed monarch's laugh, a portal to a demonic realm}}

8. Types of minions or thralls: {{random: undead and specters, cultist cabals and summoned demons, greenskin warbands, elemental guardians, demon lords and possessed initiates, fungal infestations and fungus monsters, cursed spirits and banshees and phantoms, beast packs and shapeshifters, merfolk shoals and sea monsters, thrall legions and necromancers, cannibalistic barbarians, shadow cults and void walkers, arcane assemblies and rogue enchanters, bone hordes and skeletal champions, warlock conclaves and demon swarms, toxic bloom clusters and acid spitters and sentient plants, ethereal stalkers and phase spiders, dark dwarf legions and steamwork sentinels}}

9. Behavior and personality of minions or thralls: {{random: crafty and manipulative, skittish and elusive, blindly obedient and zealously loyal, brutishly aggressive and unyieldingly stubborn, cunningly devious and patiently opportunistic, sadistically cruel and gleefully destructive, territorially defensive and suspiciously alert, fanatically devout and ritualistically precise, unpredictably wild and instinctively predatory, stoically silent and hauntingly observant}}

10. Hidden areas and their unlocking mechanisms: {{random: riddled with trickery, rare yet enticing, secured by arcane locks or puzzles of wit, lever mechanisms, pressure plates, enchanted statues demanding tribute, riddles spoken to sentient doors, blood oaths, matching elemental keystones to their respective sigils}}

11. Current status or activities of its inhabitants: {{random: holding drunken celebrations, partaking in bloody orgies, conducting clandestine rituals, forging unholy alliances, preparing for a forthcoming siege, engaging in grotesque feasts, patrolling the dark corridors, indulging in savage combat training, executing prisoners in public spectacles, performing sacrificial offerings, bickering amongst fractured factions, preparing a mass sacrifice}}

12. The effects of prolonged exposure to the dungeon's atmosphere: {{random: none, none, none, none, none, unsettling paranoia, hallucinatory visions, oppressive dread, feelings of being watched, irreversible madness, insatiable hunger, uncontrollable laughter, lingering chill, permanent shadows, creeping fungus, distorted hearing, claustrophobic tightness}}

13. Temporal anomalies and spatial distortions: {{random: none, none, none, none, none, time-dilated zones, mirrors of past and future events, areas where moments repeat endlessly, shrinking or expanding spaces, reality ripples altering perceptions of distance}}

14. How well the repuation of the player is known to the inhabitants within: {{random: unaware, unaware, vague rumors, vague rumors, familiar with past deeds, intimate knowledge}}

15. Dungeon-specific survival mechanics: {{random: none, none, none, essence-sapping miasma that withers vitality over time, mystical darkness that snuffs out light sources, whispers that unsettle the mind, warping logic and perception, gravitational anomalies that challenge every step, ley-line intersections that scramble magical energies, inhalable spores that either cause hallucinations/sickness or enlightenment}}

16. Corruption levels and sanctity status: {{random: desecrated ground and twisted idols, unhallowed whispers and faint shadows, a lingering malaise between reverence and revulsion, sanctified relics tarnished by darkness, blasphemed shrines slowly reclaiming purity, consecrated altars imbued with radiance, relics exuding divine aura, temples suffused with holy light, grounds blessed by celestial beings}}

17. The name of the dungeon/area is inspired by: {{random: DnD, Forgotten Realms, Magic the gathering, World of Warcraft, Elder Scrolls, Dark Souls, Dragon Age, The Witcher}}

